1 work ers. One member shall be the president of the Oklahoma Chapter
1
2 of the National Association of Social Workers. The remaining member
2
3 of the Board shall be selected from and shall represent the general
3
4 public.
4
5 C. Responsibility for enforcement of the provisions of this act
5
6 the Social Worker’s Licensing Act is hereby vested in the State
6
7 Board of Social Work. The Board shall have all of the duties,
7
8 powers, and authority specifically granted by, or necessary for, the
8
9 enforcement of this act the Social Worker’s Licensing Act as well as
9
10 other duties, powers, and authority it may be granted by applicable
10
11 law.
11
12 D. 1. Each member of the Board appointed as a social worker
12
13 shall:
13
14 a. be a resident of this state,
14
15 b. be licensed in good standing to engage in the practice
15
16 of social work in this state,
16
17 c. at the time of appointment, have been actively engaged
17
18 in the practice of social work for at least one (1)
18
19 year out of the last five (5) years, and
19
20 d. have at least three (3) years of experience in the
20
21 practice of social work.
21
22 2. Each member of the Board appointed to represent the general
22
23 public shall be a resident of this state who has attained the age of
23
24 majority and shall not be, nor shall ever have been, a social work
24
Req. No. 53 Page 2
1 lice nsee, or the spouse of a social work licensee, or a person who
1
2 has ever had any material financial interest in the provision of
2
3 social work services or has engaged in any activity directly related
3
4 to the practice of social work.
4
5 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
5
6 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
6
7 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
7
8 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
8
9 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
